 central galaxies in apparent\ntension with observations. These results illustrate that, even among models\nthat well reproduce many observables of the galaxy population, the $z=0$ SFS\nand other sub-populations still show marked differences that can provide strong\nconstraints on galaxy formation models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Sep 2018 18:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-27"}
